location.description: The Azure region where the reserved resource lives.

systemData.description: Metadata pertaining to creation and last modification of the resource.

reservedResourceType.description: The type of the resource that is being reserved. In addition to below types we have also added the following: OpenAIPTU, MDC, Sentinel.

billingScopeId.description: Subscription that will be charged for purchasing reservation or savings plan

quantity.description: Quantity of the skus that are part of the reservation.

appliedScopes.description: List of the subscriptions that the benefit will be applied. Do not specify if AppliedScopeType is Shared. This property will be deprecated and replaced by appliedScopeProperties instead for Single AppliedScopeType.

appliedScopeProperties.description: Properties specific to applied scope type. Not required if not applicable. Required and need to provide tenantId and managementGroupId if AppliedScopeType is ManagementGroup

renew.description: Setting this to true will automatically purchase a new reservation on the expiration date time.

reservedResourceProperties.description: Properties specific to each reserved resource type. Not required if not applicable.

reviewDateTime.description: This is the date-time when the Azure hybrid benefit needs to be reviewed.

requestDateTime.description: This is the DateTime when the reservation was initially requested for purchase.

createdDateTime.description: This is the DateTime when the reservation was created.

expiryDate.description: This is the date when the reservation will expire.

expiryDateTime.description: This is the date-time when the reservation will expire.

benefitStartTime.description: This is the DateTime when the reservation benefit started.

originalQuantity.description: Total Quantity of the skus purchased in the reservation.

planInformation.description: Information describing the type of billing plan for this reservation.

tenantId.description: Tenant ID where the savings plan should apply benefit.

managementGroupId.description: Fully-qualified identifier of the management group where the benefit must be applied.

resourceGroupId.description: Fully-qualified identifier of the resource group.

instanceFlexibility.description: Turning this on will apply the reservation discount to other VMs in the same VM size group. Only specify for VirtualMachines reserved resource type.

pricingCurrencyTotal.description: Amount of money to be paid for the Order. Tax is not included.

startDate.description: Date when the billing plan has started.

nextPaymentDueDate.description: For recurring billing plans, indicates the date when next payment will be processed. Null when total is paid off.

currencyCode.description: The ISO 4217 3-letter currency code for the currency used by this purchase record.

dueDate.description: Date when the payment needs to be done.

paymentDate.description: Date when the transaction is completed. Is null when it is scheduled.

pricingCurrencyTotal.description: Amount in pricing currency. Tax not included.

billingCurrencyTotal.description: Amount charged in Billing currency. Tax not included. Is null for future payments

billingAccount.description: Shows the Account that is charged for this payment.

status.description: Describes whether the payment is completed, failed, cancelled or scheduled in the future.

message.description: The message giving detailed information about the status code.

location.description: The Azure region where the reserved resource lives.

sku.description: The sku information associated to this reservation

properties.description: The properties associated to this reservation

kind.description: Resource Provider type to be reserved.

id.description: Fully qualified resource ID for the resource. E.g. "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/{resourceProviderNamespace}/{resourceType}/{resourceName}"

type.description: The type of the resource. E.g. "Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines" or "Microsoft.Storage/storageAccounts"

systemData.description: Azure Resource Manager metadata containing createdBy and modifiedBy information.

reservedResourceType.description: The type of the resource that is being reserved.

instanceFlexibility.description: Allows reservation discount to be applied across skus within the same auto fit group. Not all skus support instance size flexibility.

displayName.description: Friendly name for user to easily identify the reservation

archived.description: Indicates if the reservation is archived

quantity.description: Quantity of the skus that are part of the reservation.

effectiveDateTime.description: DateTime of the reservation starting when this version is effective from.

benefitStartTime.description: This is the DateTime when the reservation benefit started.

lastUpdatedDateTime.description: DateTime of the last time the reservation was updated.

expiryDate.description: This is the date when the reservation will expire.

expiryDateTime.description: This is the date-time when the reservation will expire.

reviewDateTime.description: This is the date-time when the Azure Hybrid Benefit needs to be reviewed.

skuDescription.description: Description of the sku in english.

extendedStatusInfo.description: The message giving detailed information about the status code.

billingPlan.description: The billing plan options available for this sku.

displayProvisioningState.description: The provisioning state of the reservation for display, e.g. Succeeded

provisioningSubState.description: The provisioning sub-state of the reservation, e.g. Succeeded

purchaseDate.description: This is the date when the reservation was purchased.

purchaseDateTime.description: This is the date-time when the reservation was purchased.

appliedScopeProperties.description: Properties specific to applied scope type. Not required if not applicable. Required and need to provide tenantId and managementGroupId if AppliedScopeType is ManagementGroup

billingScopeId.description: Subscription that will be charged for purchasing reservation or savings plan

renew.description: Setting this to true will automatically purchase a new reservation on the expiration date time.

renewSource.description: Reservation Id of the reservation from which this reservation is renewed. Format of the resource Id is /providers/Microsoft.Capacity/reservationOrders/{reservationOrderId}/reservations/{reservationId}.

renewDestination.description: Reservation Id of the reservation which is purchased because of renew. Format of the resource Id is /providers/Microsoft.Capacity/reservationOrders/{reservationOrderId}/reservations/{reservationId}.

renewProperties.description: The renew properties for a reservation.

userFriendlyAppliedScopeType.description: The applied scope type of the reservation for display, e.g. Shared

userFriendlyRenewState.description: The renew state of the reservation for display, e.g. On

splitDestinations.description: List of destination resource id that are created due to split. Format of the resource id is /providers/Microsoft.Capacity/reservationOrders/{reservationOrderId}/reservations/{reservationId}

splitSource.description: Resource id of the reservation from which this is split. Format of the resource id is /providers/Microsoft.Capacity/reservationOrders/{reservationOrderId}/reservations/{reservationId}

mergeDestination.description: Reservation resource id Created due to the merge. Format of the resource id is /providers/Microsoft.Capacity/reservationOrders/{reservationOrderId}/reservations/{reservationId}

mergeSources.description: Resource ids of the source reservation's merged to form this reservation. Format of the resource id is /providers/Microsoft.Capacity/reservationOrders/{reservationOrderId}/reservations/{reservationId}

swapSource.description: Resource id of the source reservation that gets swapped. Format of the resource id is /providers/microsoft.capacity/reservationOrders/{reservationOrderId}/reservations/{reservationId}

swapDestination.description: Reservation resource id that the original resource gets swapped to. Format of the resource id is /providers/microsoft.capacity/reservationOrders/{reservationOrderId}/reservations/{reservationId}

pricingCurrencyTotal.description: Amount that Microsoft uses for record. Used during refund for calculating refund limit. Tax is not included. This is locked price 30 days before expiry.

billingCurrencyTotal.description: Currency and amount that customer will be charged in customer's local currency for renewal purchase. Tax is not included.
